{{Short description|Shinto shrine in Tottori Prefecture, Japan}} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}} {{Infobox religious building | name = {{nihongo|'''Nawa Jinja'''|名和神社}} | image = Nawa-jinja Rōmon.jpg | caption = Nawa Jinja in [[Daisen, Tottori|Daisen]] | map_type = Japan | map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|35|30|16|N|133|29|42|E|source:kolossus-jawiki|display=title,inline}} | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | religious_affiliation = [[Shinto]] | type = | deity = | founded_by = | established = | date_destroyed = | location = | website = | architecture_style = | festival = | leadership = }} {{nihongo|'''Nawa Jinja'''|名和神社}} is a [[Shinto shrine]] in [[Daisen, Tottori|Daisen]], [[Tottori Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is celebrated for its [[cherry blossoms]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://yokoso.pref.tottori.jp/dd.aspx?menuid=1873 |title=Nawa Jinja |publisher=[[Tottori Prefecture]] |accessdate=23 April 2011 |url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110723211712/http://yokoso.pref.tottori.jp/dd.aspx?menuid=1873 |archivedate=23 July 2011 |df= }}</ref> It is one of the [[Fifteen Shrines of the Kenmu Restoration]], dedicated to the memory of [[Nawa Nagatoshi]].
